ts surroundings. The thermal evolution of this\nstructure seems to be dominated by radiative cooling, possibly enhanced by the\nradio-galaxy ICM interaction. We discuss several possible models for the\nformation of this SW ridge and find none of them to be entirely satisfactory.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Feb 2004 17:02:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
