ely $R^{1,2}\\times S^3$, where the $S^3$ is supported by a\nsphaleron. Finally we obtain the additional constraints implied by enhanced\nsupersymmetry, and discuss Penrose limits in the theories.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 6 Feb 2004 15:00:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 6 Jul 2004 15:55:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
